snippet.textDisplay:
Ask the question in different ways:

Under what conditions would health agencies like CDC, NIH, WHO, without being pressured, recommend lessening lockdowns?

Or: What needs to happen - what conditions need to be in place and working sustainably - to warrant "opening up the economy" without risking a renewal of pandemic forces?

Add: What parts of the pre-pandemic economy have developed accommodations and adaptations which have permitted reasonable business survival even though the pandemic has damaged most other aspects of the economy? How should these endeavors be rewarded? Should their profits from successful adaptations be rewarded in other ways besides direct financial payments?

Or: What businesses have traditionally operated on a risk/benefit ratio as part of their long term business, accepting great profits during up times and having reasonable options to prepare for down times but didn't do so, rendering them less deserving of help now? How should aid packages avoid the "privatize the profits, socialize the costs" trap?

Or: Should the States which accepted and enforced responsible actions for control and mitigation be punished financially because money appropriated to pay for these measures is also given equally to States which did not make the same sacrifices? In other words, should the noncompliant be rewarded financially equally as well as the compliant? Doesn't that send the wrong message?

In China the opening up of the various "communities" to greater access to outdoor activities was made contingent upon a clean bill of health across all elements in the community. This placed pressure upon all members of the community to engage others in compliance to social isolation rules. Is that type of reinforcement useful in distributing some types of aid assistance? For instance the right to travel by bus or train would be granted only as long as a three building community stayed in compliance. Could stimulus to the economy using direct checks to individuals be more useful if staggered into monthly allotments and be made conditional on compliance with certain hygiene and social isolation behaviors by all members of the community?

Or: What measures have been put into place to pair financial assistance with a full public report of the names of the recipients and the submission of the areas used by the assistance if it is essentially rendered as a free handout? Most government salaries and benefits are made public. Is this financial aid not the same or very similar? Unless there is going to be some control over cash handouts, what expectations can be put forward for such largesse if no feedback on its usefullness is generated?

Or: What measures have been baked into aid packages to prevent waste, fraud and abuse prior to the handouts?

Along the same line: If an imaginary "pay-go" was applied prior to appropriating any financial assistance in these trillions of dollars passed or already accessed from reserved accounts, where would the "pay" part come from and what would that mean to our national debt? To what extent is any of this budget busting being subjected to a financial analysis using costs and benefit questions? How will the low payment of income tax on profits by corporations (down pre-pandemic to just 7% versus the 93% paid by individual income tax payers, according to the Treasury Dept figures) be adjusted to mirror the previous lowering of the tax burden on corporations if those same corporations accept further generousity from Federal handouts?

snippet.textDisplay:
The rest of the world is sacrificing for containment. How will they deal with Americans that come from Trump's America? Make them isolate for 14 days, sequester goods for four days, prohibit U.S. planes from their airports? Thinking scenarios through is not one of Trump's strengths. He operates by fraud and coercion and that is anathema in public health.

So-called third world countries like India are making Trump transparent as a self-indulgent fool who has no more sense of duty and sacrifice than his 'bone spurs' can allow. If systematic testing is ever allowed in America under Trump it will be possible to attribute tens or hundreds of thousands of unnecessary deaths to Trump's arrogant stupidity. So expect an even more frantic resistance to widespread testing by Trump.

This is all so obvious to non-Americans. Even U.S. news media will ignore the testing issue to highlight some gossip or superstition fuelled bit of momentary nonsense. And thats another hundred thousand or so needless deaths to attribute to the 'perfect storm' of COVID-19 in America. Cultures that have persisted for many centuries, some for a millennia or more, have a degree of reverence for their elderly. Trump thinks of them as disposable.
